ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If you have any interest in particle physics, TAKE THIS COURSE.

If you want to learn particle physics and you're game to teach yourself a lot to fill in the gaps in the lecture material, then take it. If it's only a passing interest in particle physics, maybe not.
Take it! It's chill compared with undergrad physics classes, but you will learn a lot. The material is difficult but the assignments are doable.
It is a great course on particle physics. I would highly recommend it.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Many of these topics will be included in my thesis...

This was so, so, so helpful for understanding the material in my senior thesis. I left this class with a fantastic understanding of how detectors work and the basic forces and computation of matrix elements and terms in the QCD Lagrangian, etc. Very helpful.
